#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:3
#: 4541d8fc210d447989bfd9f155961236
msgid "Migrate Windows qubes from old Qubes versions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:6
#: 0d14e2d4251b4d8cb7c1bd7c1b8a58a1
msgid ""
"For Windows 7, 10, and 11, there is a way to migrate backups created under "
"Qubes R4.1 to R4.2. For this, a backup must be created under R4.1, and this "
"backup has to be restored under Qubes R4.2, resulting in a VM well "
"integrated into Qubes R4.2. If ``qvm-features <VMname> audio-model ich6`` is"
" set, Windows will even have audio, although for Windows 10 and 11, it is "
"somewhat scratchy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:10
#: d6665b7fc9a24460adb99adc4acaf25a
msgid "Preparation"
msgstr "Préparation"

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:13
#: 4481f3ad4e5941bab5102b190b135cac
msgid ""
"While this is somewhat straightforward, things get difficult if QWT 4.1.68-1"
" (or earlier) was installed in the VM. Prior to creating the backup, this "
"old version has to be removed, which can be quite tricky for Windows 10 and "
"11. Otherwise, the restored backup will probably not start or run under "
"Qubes R4.2, because this QWT version is incompatible with R4.2."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:15
#: 942b7c98d23d487698d9022c63b7f704
msgid ""
"To uninstall the installed QWT version, proceed as described in the "
":doc:`QWT installation documentation for R4.2 "
"</user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-tools>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:19
#: b6ad13fb87214c00a2a3ee02952168f5
msgid "Transferring the Windows Qube"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:22
#: 1efa72df9fb54a5a94b27a3b7222e966
msgid "Now, the backup for R4.2 may be created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:24
#: ce56d18a0dd74f6989ab6c8050531280
msgid "This backup can be installed in Qubes R4.2 and will (probably) work."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:26
#: dc6dd9ab107c47cc919240d3f0eed223
msgid ""
"If Qubes Windows Tools was installed under R4.1, the new version for R4.2 "
"can then be installed as described in the documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:29
#: 8c55a267e5a54c9bad699a3954026c74
msgid ""
"**Note:** The Qubes application menus for the newly restored Windows qubes "
"will be empty, but can be easily restored via the Qube Manager or by issuing"
" the command ``qubes-sync-appmenus`` in ``dom0``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:33
#: fd2ca59053c14ffea9c7724f193b697e
msgid "Migration to Qubes R4.3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:36
#: 4ab5eb28a54a4001b2932aa03c1e7a9c
msgid ""
"As the current new QWT version was developed primarily for Qubes R4.3, it is"
" compatible with the version of Qubes. So, a Windows VM running under Qubes "
"R4.2 should be transferable to R4.3 via backup/restore, without the need to "
"remove and reinstall Qubes Windows Tools. At least, for the current pre-"
"release of Qubes R4.3-rc1, this is possible. Currently, however, the new "
"Qubes graphics driver is still very buggy, especially for Windows 11, so it "
"is better not to use it there, since seamless mode is quite unreliable "
"there, and changing the screen resolution may put the VM into an unusable "
"state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/templates/windows/qubes-windows-migrate.rst:38
#: 542b1bf83ad446d196d00f24b601a303
msgid ""
"Performing an in-place upgrade of Qubes itself from R4.2.4 to R4.3-rc1 "
"preserves the functionality of Windows 7, 10, and 11 qubes including Qubes "
"Windows Tools; so there is no need to perform an upgrade of these qubes. If,"
" for Windos 10 or 11, the Qubes graphics driver was installed, its "
"performance and (current) bugginess may change, however."
msgstr ""
